1
00:00:34,894 --> 00:00:35,824
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:35,824 --> 00:00:36,825
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:36,825 --> 00:00:38,356
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:38,356 --> 00:00:40,442
[Episode 3]

5
00:00:47,068 --> 00:00:49,699
Excuse me.

6
00:01:07,735 --> 00:01:09,976
Hello, sir.

7
00:01:09,976 --> 00:01:11,616
So this is where you've been.

8
00:01:11,616 --> 00:01:14,066
You got here faster than I thought.

9
00:01:15,109 --> 00:01:16,894
Wait here. I'll grab you something to wear.

10
00:01:16,894 --> 00:01:18,904
No, I'm okay...

11
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:51,735
You looked better before you changed.

12
00:01:51,735 --> 00:01:53,181
Less douchey.

13
00:01:53,181 --> 00:01:55,524
Go inside and change.

14
00:02:26,331 --> 00:02:28,031
So why'd you come find me?

15
00:02:28,031 --> 00:02:30,851
Aren't you curious how I found you?

16
00:02:30,851 --> 00:02:33,770
Someone's been tailing me
for the past few days.

17
00:02:41,187 --> 00:02:43,207
[Freshness that wins hearts]

18
00:02:59,651 --> 00:03:01,276
<i>What now?</i>

19
00:03:01,276 --> 00:03:03,550
<i>Am I busted?</i>

20
00:03:06,485 --> 00:03:08,311
<i>Hey, Ju Young Jae.</i>

21
00:03:08,311 --> 00:03:10,109
<i>It's been a while.</i>

22
00:03:10,109 --> 00:03:11,911
<i>- He got caught?</i>
- Sorry, Soo Bin.

23
00:03:11,911 --> 00:03:14,019
He asked me to keep it a secret.

24
00:03:17,223 --> 00:03:19,191
You scared me.

25
00:03:19,191 --> 00:03:22,069
I've got a thing about flowers.

26
00:03:23,485 --> 00:03:25,148
That's why I brought it.

27
00:03:25,148 --> 00:03:26,907
Go ahead, hit me.

28
00:03:40,396 --> 00:03:41,998
Thanks to you,

29
00:03:41,998 --> 00:03:46,093
our show hit its highest ratings ever.

30
00:03:46,836 --> 00:03:48,234
So as a thank-you,

31
00:03:48,234 --> 00:03:51,924
I came to ask if you'd come
on the show one more time.

32
00:03:51,924 --> 00:03:54,043
That's a strange way to show thanks.

33
00:03:54,043 --> 00:03:55,136
I'm asking you.

34
00:03:55,136 --> 00:03:56,883
You came all this way just for that?

35
00:03:56,883 --> 00:03:59,318
Well, why'd you turn your phone off?

36
00:03:59,318 --> 00:04:01,193
But hey...

37
00:04:01,193 --> 00:04:03,526
I got to come back home for once.

38
00:04:03,526 --> 00:04:05,063
It's nice.

39
00:04:05,063 --> 00:04:07,023
All thanks to you.

40
00:04:07,023 --> 00:04:08,876
I was hoping for more.

41
00:04:11,176 --> 00:04:12,697
Huh? Your phone works just fine.

42
00:04:12,697 --> 00:04:14,917
Was Jin Su's place called Feast or something?

43
00:04:14,917 --> 00:04:16,199
Where was it again?

44
00:04:16,199 --> 00:04:18,075
Why don't you just look it up
on that working phone?

45
00:04:18,075 --> 00:04:19,685
You're right.

46
00:04:20,369 --> 00:04:22,179
See you, then.

47
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,605
Director!

48
00:04:24,605 --> 00:04:25,620
Director!

49
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:27,109
Wait!

50
00:04:27,109 --> 00:04:28,340
Director, let me drive you!

51
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:30,671
Hold on!

52
00:04:30,671 --> 00:04:34,020
If you show up one more time,
my whole life could change.

53
00:04:34,020 --> 00:04:35,679
Take a right at that intersection.

54
00:04:35,679 --> 00:04:37,219
First, my pay goes up.

55
00:04:37,219 --> 00:04:40,400
Then I'd have a steady income,
so I could cut back on out-of-town gigs.

56
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:43,526
I get so much out of this,
I can't even list it all.

57
00:04:43,526 --> 00:04:45,280
Are you okay with me doing the show?

58
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,540
Of course I am!

59
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:48,580
My life gets a major upgrade out of this.

60
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:51,199
Personal feelings? Who cares.

61
00:04:52,452 --> 00:04:53,932
Did Producer Kyung tell you that?

62
00:04:53,932 --> 00:04:55,933
That your life gets better if I do it?

63
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:57,914
So you'll do it?

64
00:05:01,151 --> 00:05:03,532
<i>Soo Bin, what do I do?</i>

65
00:05:03,532 --> 00:05:06,292
<i>I don't think I can make it today.</i>

66
00:05:06,292 --> 00:05:08,651
Have you eaten?

67
00:05:08,651 --> 00:05:10,533
Do you want to grab a bite?

68
00:05:12,463 --> 00:05:14,048
Enjoy.

69
00:05:14,048 --> 00:05:15,091
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

70
00:05:15,091 --> 00:05:16,917
Thanks for the food.

71
00:05:32,716 --> 00:05:35,151
Why couldn't your mom make it?

72
00:05:35,151 --> 00:05:37,338
- Yeah, I don't know.
- Why not just go to her place?

73
00:05:37,338 --> 00:05:39,274
Why are you meeting her outside?

74
00:05:40,282 --> 00:05:41,840
Yeah...

75
00:05:53,193 --> 00:05:54,422
You mean the day after tomorrow.

76
00:05:54,422 --> 00:05:55,901
- Thanks for the meal.
- Yeah.

77
00:05:55,901 --> 00:05:58,526
- Jin Su's doing well, right?
- Of course.

78
00:05:58,526 --> 00:06:00,344
Same as always.

79
00:06:00,344 --> 00:06:01,990
I'm so sorry, sir.

80
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,319
Please, don't say that.

81
00:06:03,319 --> 00:06:05,899
- Come again.
- I will.

82
00:06:08,193 --> 00:06:11,649
Even if you call me last-minute,
I'll be right there.

83
00:06:11,649 --> 00:06:13,859
You keep calling on me, so of course I will.

84
00:06:13,859 --> 00:06:15,860
Yes, sir. Thank you.

85
00:06:15,860 --> 00:06:18,863
Take care.

86
00:06:18,863 --> 00:06:20,978
They're booking you
for a festival two days out?

87
00:06:20,978 --> 00:06:22,998
It has to be a fill-in gig.

88
00:06:22,998 --> 00:06:26,078
Works for me, though. Fill-ins pay better.

89
00:06:26,078 --> 00:06:28,038
That's how hard I'm hustling.

90
00:06:28,038 --> 00:06:31,174
But if you'd just come on the show?

91
00:06:36,046 --> 00:06:38,132
See? It's peak festival season.

92
00:06:38,132 --> 00:06:40,225
Wait, no. It's Producer Kyung.

93
00:06:41,538 --> 00:06:43,259
- Yes, Producer Kyung.
<i>- Hey, Yi Jae.</i>

94
00:06:43,259 --> 00:06:45,158
<i>Why haven't you reported back?</i>

95
00:06:45,158 --> 00:06:47,023
<i>Is he doing it?</i>

96
00:06:47,624 --> 00:06:49,545
I'm talking to him right now.

97
00:06:49,545 --> 00:06:51,765
He seems pretty busy with his next project.

98
00:06:51,765 --> 00:06:53,145
We're working out the schedule.

99
00:06:53,145 --> 00:06:55,804
<i>What if we get axed before that?</i>

100
00:06:55,804 --> 00:06:57,651
<i>Hurry it up already.</i>

101
00:06:57,651 --> 00:07:00,537
I'm working on it.

102
00:07:01,401 --> 00:07:04,124
Why are you so impatient?

103
00:07:05,721 --> 00:07:08,412
- If I go on the show, will things change?
- Hey!

104
00:07:08,412 --> 00:07:10,915
<i>- What?</i>
- If I go on the show,

105
00:07:10,915 --> 00:07:12,145
will Ju Yi Jae's life change?

106
00:07:12,145 --> 00:07:15,085
Hey, are you crazy? What's wrong with you?

107
00:07:15,085 --> 00:07:16,159
What?

108
00:07:16,159 --> 00:07:18,819
You said if I went on the show,
your life would get easier.

109
00:07:18,819 --> 00:07:21,099
So that's what I'm doing.

110
00:07:22,610 --> 00:07:24,978
I'll do the show.

111
00:07:47,777 --> 00:07:50,462
Yes, order coming up!

112
00:07:51,621 --> 00:07:53,568
It's two portions,
but I made it more like three.

113
00:07:53,568 --> 00:07:56,176
That one's on the house.

114
00:07:58,276 --> 00:07:59,942
The sashimi's drying out. Where is he?

115
00:07:59,942 --> 00:08:03,193
Sir, we need to hire someone.

116
00:08:03,193 --> 00:08:04,426
Sorry about that.

117
00:08:04,426 --> 00:08:06,554
[SimSim Fisheries]
Here's your sashimi bowl.

118
00:08:06,554 --> 00:08:09,735
- Some side dishes too.
- Sure, I'll bring more.

119
00:08:09,735 --> 00:08:10,401
Hey!

120
00:08:10,401 --> 00:08:12,193
It was great.

121
00:08:12,193 --> 00:08:14,234
I'll pay.

122
00:08:14,234 --> 00:08:15,426
Oh, okay.

123
00:08:15,426 --> 00:08:17,906
- Did you enjoy your meal?
- Yes.

124
00:08:18,734 --> 00:08:19,901
Who is this?

125
00:08:19,901 --> 00:08:21,193
[To SimSim Fisheries, stay healthy, Sim Yu Geon]
You know who this is?

126
00:08:21,193 --> 00:08:23,042
- No idea.
- A singer or something?

127
00:08:23,042 --> 00:08:25,234
That's the owner's son.

128
00:08:25,234 --> 00:08:26,282
Handsome, right?

129
00:08:26,282 --> 00:08:28,909
I thought you were his son.

130
00:08:28,909 --> 00:08:34,276
He does look like...

131
00:08:34,276 --> 00:08:35,762
the owner, though.

132
00:08:35,762 --> 00:08:38,162
We went to school together too.

133
00:08:38,162 --> 00:08:39,378
You here visiting?

134
00:08:39,378 --> 00:08:42,276
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

135
00:08:42,276 --> 00:08:44,183
Your son is famous?

136
00:08:44,183 --> 00:08:47,318
Yeah, my son's an actor.

137
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:48,670
- An actor?
- Really?

138
00:08:48,670 --> 00:08:49,710
What's he been in?

139
00:08:49,710 --> 00:08:52,234
He debuted as Friend Three
in "Devil High School,"

140
00:08:52,234 --> 00:08:55,102
stole the show in episode four,
scene 27 of "The Young Master in My Garden,"

141
00:08:55,102 --> 00:08:56,854
and delivered a legendary line

142
00:08:56,854 --> 00:09:00,357
just before the episode eight finale
of "I Won't Love Anymore."

143
00:09:00,357 --> 00:09:03,486
"Director, the car's ready for you."

144
00:09:03,486 --> 00:09:05,870
And many, many more.

145
00:09:08,526 --> 00:09:10,386
- You seen it?
- You seen any?

146
00:09:10,386 --> 00:09:12,578
- We've been here too long. Let's go.
- Thanks for the meal.

147
00:09:12,578 --> 00:09:13,727
- Yeah, it was great.
- Thanks for the meal.

148
00:09:13,727 --> 00:09:14,727
- Come again.
- Thanks.

149
00:09:14,727 --> 00:09:17,249
- Come again!
- Yeah.

150
00:09:17,249 --> 00:09:19,307
They haven't seen any of it.
Take all that down.

151
00:09:19,307 --> 00:09:20,697
Yes.

152
00:09:23,631 --> 00:09:25,882
[To SimSim Fisheries, stay healthy,
Sim Yu Geon]

153
00:09:30,359 --> 00:09:33,440
You look gorgeous in this, Ha Na.

154
00:09:42,769 --> 00:09:46,320
I wonder where he's striking poses this time.

155
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:50,373
[First Love's Smile]
[Casting Audition]

156
00:10:00,068 --> 00:10:02,343
Sim Yu Geon.

157
00:10:03,651 --> 00:10:04,818
Yes.

158
00:10:04,818 --> 00:10:07,098
Yes, come on in.

159
00:10:18,224 --> 00:10:22,815
<i>You're not quite
the right fit for the character.</i>

160
00:10:22,815 --> 00:10:24,630
<i>Marriage?</i>

161
00:10:25,735 --> 00:10:28,029
<i>I thought I made myself clear.</i>

162
00:10:28,029 --> 00:10:29,154
<i>Then kill him.</i>

163
00:10:29,154 --> 00:10:30,955
[Casting Director]
<i>Yes.</i>

164
00:10:32,443 --> 00:10:34,085
<i>Sir...</i>

165
00:10:34,818 --> 00:10:38,068
<i>Can you be certain we're alive?</i>

166
00:10:38,068 --> 00:10:39,624
<i>Next.</i>

167
00:10:39,624 --> 00:10:41,316
<i>That was a bit disappointing.</i>

168
00:11:04,769 --> 00:11:06,358
Ha Na,

169
00:11:06,358 --> 00:11:09,369
your revised schedule's in.

170
00:11:11,942 --> 00:11:13,901
Hold on, Director Kang.

171
00:11:13,901 --> 00:11:15,409
Yes?

172
00:11:15,409 --> 00:11:17,456
Why am I the only one off that day?

173
00:11:17,456 --> 00:11:20,839
Is there something else on my schedule
I don't know about?

174
00:11:21,456 --> 00:11:26,670
That day, you have
a joint event with the CEO...

175
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:28,756
What is it this time?

176
00:11:28,756 --> 00:11:31,056
You need to go accept the major donor award.

177
00:11:31,056 --> 00:11:32,876
Excuse us.

178
00:11:32,876 --> 00:11:34,701
Let's step out.

179
00:11:34,701 --> 00:11:37,242
A picture-perfect mother-daughter moment,

180
00:11:37,242 --> 00:11:39,566
wouldn't that be lovely?

181
00:11:41,477 --> 00:11:45,064
The exemplary mom is the one getting the award.
Why do I have to go?

182
00:11:45,064 --> 00:11:46,774
So I can be your accessory again?

183
00:11:46,774 --> 00:11:49,141
Does that bother you?

184
00:11:49,141 --> 00:11:51,502
Hey, why would that bother you? It's an honor.

185
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:55,181
I'm bothered because you don't get
why I'm bothered.

186
00:11:55,181 --> 00:11:56,821
You think it ends with me skipping out?

187
00:11:56,821 --> 00:11:59,245
When shooting gets pushed back,
who has to deal with it?

188
00:11:59,245 --> 00:12:01,205
The crew and the other actors, that's who.

189
00:12:01,205 --> 00:12:04,722
That's part of their job.

190
00:12:04,722 --> 00:12:08,212
People with power get to dictate time, too.

191
00:12:08,212 --> 00:12:10,543
Doesn't it embarrass you? Living like that?

192
00:12:10,543 --> 00:12:13,882
I'm so happy you get to live off
your mom's success.

193
00:12:13,882 --> 00:12:16,053
Makes me feel
like all that hard work was worth it.

194
00:12:16,053 --> 00:12:19,302
It's that "living off Mom" talk
that makes me miserable.

195
00:12:19,302 --> 00:12:20,432
Oh, you brat.

196
00:12:20,432 --> 00:12:23,234
You don't even know
what real misery looks like.

197
00:12:25,026 --> 00:12:27,648
If you go around apologizing
on set again like last time,

198
00:12:27,648 --> 00:12:29,818
you think people will respect you for that?

199
00:12:29,818 --> 00:12:31,148
It just makes you look weak.

200
00:12:31,148 --> 00:12:33,904
No, Mom, you're the one making me look weak.

201
00:12:33,904 --> 00:12:35,948
When you mess up, of course you apologize.

202
00:12:35,948 --> 00:12:38,314
And my screw-ups are
usually because of you anyway.

203
00:12:38,314 --> 00:12:39,318
Keep your voice down.

204
00:12:39,318 --> 00:12:42,795
There are rats everywhere out there
trying to dig up dirt.

205
00:12:44,485 --> 00:12:46,388
Oh, CEO An,

206
00:12:46,388 --> 00:12:47,548
I'm so sorry.

207
00:12:47,548 --> 00:12:48,877
I'm a little late, aren't I?

208
00:12:48,877 --> 00:12:51,028
I know you've been waiting a while for me.

209
00:12:51,028 --> 00:12:52,070
So thoughtful.

210
00:12:52,070 --> 00:12:54,877
By the way, who's the girl
doing my Ha Na's hair?

211
00:12:54,877 --> 00:12:56,177
I've never seen her before.

212
00:12:56,177 --> 00:12:57,859
She was originally assigned to Si Hyun,

213
00:12:57,859 --> 00:12:59,651
but she's quick and has a great eye, so...

214
00:12:59,651 --> 00:13:01,316
Swap her out.

215
00:13:01,316 --> 00:13:02,397
Look at that hair.

216
00:13:02,397 --> 00:13:04,268
No taste at all.

217
00:13:04,268 --> 00:13:06,176
Now.

218
00:13:06,176 --> 00:13:08,029
Yes.

219
00:13:12,651 --> 00:13:15,193
Are you serious? Soo Bin is back in town?

220
00:13:15,193 --> 00:13:18,282
Yeah, he just had bibimbap
at our place a little while ago.

221
00:13:18,282 --> 00:13:19,917
And he was with Yi Jae too.

222
00:13:19,917 --> 00:13:22,460
Oh my.

223
00:13:23,326 --> 00:13:27,333
Didn't Director Woo send him off
to the States for school?

224
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:28,834
He never showed his face around here,

225
00:13:28,834 --> 00:13:30,901
so I figured he was off being a doctor.

226
00:13:30,901 --> 00:13:35,568
So that film director who was on Yi Jae's show
is really Director Woo's son?

227
00:13:35,568 --> 00:13:37,092
That's what I'm saying.

228
00:13:37,092 --> 00:13:40,234
He changed his whole name.
I almost didn't recognize him.

229
00:13:40,234 --> 00:13:41,972
Why did he suddenly become a Lee?

230
00:13:41,972 --> 00:13:43,635
Lee An Woo, was it?

231
00:13:43,635 --> 00:13:45,454
Or Lee An Ku?

232
00:13:45,454 --> 00:13:46,934
It's really something.

233
00:13:46,934 --> 00:13:50,735
Yi Jae was the one who was always
running around saying she'd make movies.

234
00:13:50,735 --> 00:13:52,262
How did it end up the other way around?

235
00:13:52,262 --> 00:13:53,526
I know, right?

236
00:13:53,526 --> 00:13:55,068
Soo Bin is staying at my place.

237
00:13:55,068 --> 00:13:56,266
- Oh my, you scared me.
- Oh my goodness!

238
00:13:56,266 --> 00:13:57,613
Hey.

239
00:13:57,613 --> 00:13:59,406
What are you doing sitting here?

240
00:13:59,406 --> 00:14:00,616
Waiting for the bus.

241
00:14:00,616 --> 00:14:03,443
Oh, I see.

242
00:14:03,443 --> 00:14:05,187
Oh look. Here they come.

243
00:14:05,187 --> 00:14:05,787
- Oh my.
- Oh my.

244
00:14:05,787 --> 00:14:07,234
- That's them.
- Yi Jae.

245
00:14:07,234 --> 00:14:10,048
It really is them.

246
00:14:11,664 --> 00:14:14,276
See, I told you.

247
00:14:14,276 --> 00:14:17,777
Those two have always been joined at the hip.

248
00:14:17,777 --> 00:14:19,193
How sweet.

249
00:14:19,193 --> 00:14:23,326
But you don't run the guesthouse anymore.

250
00:14:23,326 --> 00:14:26,441
Figured he had his reasons.

251
00:14:27,485 --> 00:14:28,818
The bus is here.

252
00:14:28,818 --> 00:14:29,686
Right.

253
00:14:29,686 --> 00:14:31,832
- Don't get up. Keep doing what you're doing.
- Okay.

254
00:14:31,832 --> 00:14:34,323
- I'm off.
- Bye.

255
00:14:36,568 --> 00:14:38,610
Grandma Jong Sun!

256
00:14:38,610 --> 00:14:41,276
Grandma Jong Sun!

257
00:14:41,276 --> 00:14:43,735
She's not here.

258
00:14:43,735 --> 00:14:45,443
You give it to her.

259
00:14:45,443 --> 00:14:46,788
Sure.

260
00:14:46,788 --> 00:14:48,855
Hold on a sec.

261
00:15:05,056 --> 00:15:06,759
Here.

262
00:15:06,759 --> 00:15:08,941
[Gyeongseong Love Song]
I'm giving this back to you.

263
00:15:12,610 --> 00:15:13,920
You gave me this script

264
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,919
and said you'd wait.

265
00:15:15,919 --> 00:15:18,618
I think it belongs with you now.

266
00:15:21,039 --> 00:15:24,082
So now you're returning my dream?

267
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,699
You sure about that?

268
00:15:26,699 --> 00:15:29,599
What if I rip it up or burn it?

269
00:15:29,599 --> 00:15:32,965
If that's the ending you want, then do it.

270
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:36,169
I overlooked the fact
that I'm someone from your past

271
00:15:36,169 --> 00:15:38,770
and only thought about moving forward.

272
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:41,330
I was wrong.

273
00:15:41,330 --> 00:15:45,103
The ending of our story should've
come before the script's ending.

274
00:15:45,735 --> 00:15:48,263
I'm sorry. I really mean it.

275
00:15:50,876 --> 00:15:54,463
I'm sorry I didn't see it myself,

276
00:15:54,463 --> 00:15:56,823
and I'm sorry it took so long.

277
00:15:58,450 --> 00:16:01,859
Those years of waiting you talked about,

278
00:16:01,859 --> 00:16:05,916
they were years I didn't want to remember.

279
00:16:09,151 --> 00:16:11,026
<i>All because of that?</i>

280
00:16:11,026 --> 00:16:12,315
<i>You tanked your college
entrance exam over this?</i>

281
00:16:12,315 --> 00:16:14,166
<i>You let a girl ruin your future?</i>

282
00:16:14,166 --> 00:16:15,584
<i>It wasn't because of Yi Jae.</i>

283
00:16:15,584 --> 00:16:17,615
<i>I never wanted to go to medical school.</i>

284
00:16:17,615 --> 00:16:18,359
<i>Soo Bin.</i>

285
00:16:18,359 --> 00:16:20,359
<i>- You little!
- Please stop!</i>

286
00:16:20,359 --> 00:16:21,716
<i>Mom!</i>

287
00:16:21,716 --> 00:16:24,934
<i>No!</i>

288
00:16:27,818 --> 00:16:28,974
<i>Hit me.</i>

289
00:16:28,974 --> 00:16:31,023
<i>Until you've gotten it all out.</i>

290
00:16:33,651 --> 00:16:35,859
As punishment,

291
00:16:35,859 --> 00:16:39,357
my father tried to ship me off to the States,

292
00:16:39,357 --> 00:16:42,444
and until I told him myself that I'd obey him,

293
00:16:42,444 --> 00:16:45,288
I wasn't even allowed to leave the house.

294
00:16:51,401 --> 00:16:53,713
It only took ten days.

295
00:16:54,568 --> 00:16:57,383
For me to give up on myself.

296
00:17:00,693 --> 00:17:02,651
<i>I'll go.</i>

297
00:17:02,651 --> 00:17:04,359
<i>To the States.</i>

298
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:07,435
<i>I'll live the way you want me to.</i>

299
00:17:11,265 --> 00:17:12,912
<i>Good.</i>

300
00:17:13,934 --> 00:17:16,188
<i>That's how it should be.</i>

301
00:17:19,151 --> 00:17:20,933
But,

302
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:25,000
how could you not give up on me
when I'd given up on myself?

303
00:17:26,735 --> 00:17:29,449
That huge heart of yours

304
00:17:29,449 --> 00:17:32,376
made me even more ashamed of myself.

305
00:17:35,607 --> 00:17:41,169
I'm not asking you
to understand now, or to forgive me.

306
00:17:42,151 --> 00:17:43,901
I just

307
00:17:43,901 --> 00:17:48,351
wanted you to feel a little better.

308
00:17:49,651 --> 00:17:51,471
Right.

309
00:17:51,471 --> 00:17:53,767
That's a relief.

310
00:17:53,767 --> 00:17:56,275
So it wasn't my fault.

311
00:17:57,006 --> 00:18:00,071
There were circumstances you couldn't help.

312
00:18:00,693 --> 00:18:02,590
I see.

313
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:13,084
But I don't feel better.

314
00:18:14,610 --> 00:18:16,526
You're hitting me with this now

315
00:18:16,526 --> 00:18:18,881
and calling it comfort?

316
00:18:20,026 --> 00:18:22,544
You know the worst way

317
00:18:22,544 --> 00:18:26,191
to be remembered by someone you loved?

318
00:18:26,191 --> 00:18:28,068
Not as the bad guy,

319
00:18:28,068 --> 00:18:30,768
but as a pathetic loser.

320
00:18:31,491 --> 00:18:33,674
You pathetic bastard.

321
00:18:57,634 --> 00:18:58,872
Hey!

322
00:18:58,872 --> 00:19:00,240
Huh?

323
00:19:02,443 --> 00:19:03,503
You're back.

324
00:19:03,503 --> 00:19:05,670
I washed that to put barley tea in,

325
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:07,401
and you went and stuck flowers in it!

326
00:19:07,401 --> 00:19:09,841
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

327
00:19:09,841 --> 00:19:11,302
- Did you eat?
- Not yet.

328
00:19:11,302 --> 00:19:14,234
What were you doing that you haven't eaten yet?

329
00:19:14,234 --> 00:19:16,389
I was waiting to eat with you.

330
00:19:16,389 --> 00:19:17,542
You sweet talker.

331
00:19:17,542 --> 00:19:18,821
- Let's go inside.
- Okay.

332
00:19:18,821 --> 00:19:20,522
The yard looks clean, doesn't it?

333
00:19:20,522 --> 00:19:22,151
It does look nice.

334
00:19:22,151 --> 00:19:23,988
- Good job.
- Yeah.

335
00:19:26,942 --> 00:19:29,151
You could've called ahead.

336
00:19:29,151 --> 00:19:30,946
I would've made something for you.

337
00:19:30,946 --> 00:19:32,955
Noodles are fine.

338
00:19:35,109 --> 00:19:37,244
I'm still having no luck with the deposit.

339
00:19:37,244 --> 00:19:39,151
Tell the landlord to wait a bit longer.

340
00:19:39,151 --> 00:19:40,330
If worst comes to worst,

341
00:19:40,330 --> 00:19:42,406
I'll just put the shop up for sale.

342
00:19:42,406 --> 00:19:44,626
You said you'd buy the house back.

343
00:19:44,626 --> 00:19:46,326
Now the shop's on the market too?

344
00:19:46,326 --> 00:19:47,866
I'll figure it out.

345
00:19:47,866 --> 00:19:50,421
- Do you think you can?
- I'll just have to find a way.

346
00:19:51,299 --> 00:19:52,901
When will you have it?

347
00:19:52,901 --> 00:19:55,853
I feel terrible making excuses every time.

348
00:19:56,513 --> 00:19:58,856
What about me? Aren't you sorry?

349
00:20:00,124 --> 00:20:03,771
I gave up on feeling sorry for you
because there's just no end to it.

350
00:20:03,771 --> 00:20:07,404
I'm sorry you got stuck with me as a mother.

351
00:20:07,404 --> 00:20:08,525
You better pay me back.

352
00:20:08,525 --> 00:20:10,164
It's not a gift.

353
00:20:10,164 --> 00:20:11,985
You know what this money means to me, right?

354
00:20:11,985 --> 00:20:14,859
I earned this money on boats,
up mountains, and in the mud.

355
00:20:14,859 --> 00:20:17,610
Of course, I know.

356
00:20:17,610 --> 00:20:19,418
But...

357
00:20:20,328 --> 00:20:22,838
I saw him on your show.

358
00:20:25,401 --> 00:20:27,426
I'm done.

359
00:20:30,859 --> 00:20:31,965
Mom.

360
00:20:31,965 --> 00:20:34,108
Did you know I hit my highest ratings yet?

361
00:20:34,108 --> 00:20:37,087
I'm practically the MVP of our show right now.

362
00:20:37,087 --> 00:20:38,930
Producer Kyung loves me,

363
00:20:38,930 --> 00:20:40,808
and the executive producer
absolutely adores me.

364
00:20:40,808 --> 00:20:42,227
Really?

365
00:20:42,227 --> 00:20:43,810
Well, they should be giving you a raise,

366
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:46,272
not just showering you with compliments.

367
00:20:46,272 --> 00:20:47,857
Of course they will!

368
00:20:47,857 --> 00:20:48,901
Who do you think I am?

369
00:20:48,901 --> 00:20:51,193
I'm Park Hyun Ok's daughter, Ju Yi Jae!

370
00:20:51,193 --> 00:20:53,587
Girl, you are all talk.

371
00:20:53,587 --> 00:20:55,448
- Leave it, I'll do it.
- No, get out of the way.

372
00:20:55,448 --> 00:20:58,327
- I said I got it.
- Move.

373
00:20:58,327 --> 00:21:02,005
Mom, since when are you so strong?

374
00:21:02,005 --> 00:21:04,791
- I've got it.
- What've you been eating?

375
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:07,716
What else would I eat? Just rice.

376
00:21:23,193 --> 00:21:25,943
Don't you dare tell Mom about this.

377
00:21:28,193 --> 00:21:30,448
I need extra pay to keep quiet.

378
00:21:33,126 --> 00:21:34,942
You got caught and you're still this shameless?

379
00:21:34,942 --> 00:21:36,745
Pleasure doing business with you.

380
00:21:49,918 --> 00:21:52,671
[2011 Bunam Youth Film Festival Grand Prize
Winner, Ju Yi Jae]

381
00:21:56,299 --> 00:21:58,454
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

382
00:22:04,265 --> 00:22:07,034
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

383
00:22:09,454 --> 00:22:12,318
This cold raw fish soup is on the house.

384
00:22:12,318 --> 00:22:15,777
Look at you. You've gotten even more handsome.

385
00:22:15,777 --> 00:22:18,235
It just makes me so happy
to see you after all this time.

386
00:22:18,235 --> 00:22:19,276
Right?

387
00:22:19,276 --> 00:22:21,693
I'm so happy too.

388
00:22:21,693 --> 00:22:23,410
- Thank you.
- Sure.

389
00:22:23,410 --> 00:22:24,410
Thank you.

390
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:27,129
Don't mention it. It's not much.

391
00:22:27,129 --> 00:22:29,249
Enjoy your meal. Okay.

392
00:22:29,249 --> 00:22:30,458
Eat up, son.

393
00:22:30,458 --> 00:22:31,994
You too, Mom.

394
00:22:31,994 --> 00:22:35,054
You love wrapping it in white kimchi.

395
00:22:36,924 --> 00:22:38,068
Here, open up.

396
00:22:38,068 --> 00:22:40,351
- Ah.
- Ah.

397
00:22:42,023 --> 00:22:43,303
Is it good?

398
00:22:43,303 --> 00:22:46,182
Everything tastes better when you feed me.

399
00:22:46,182 --> 00:22:48,268
It's been forever since I had raw fish.

400
00:22:48,268 --> 00:22:50,103
That's just because you eat fancy now, right?

401
00:22:50,103 --> 00:22:55,023
Eating with you is the best thing
in the world to me.

402
00:22:55,023 --> 00:22:57,584
I'm sorry I didn't keep in touch more often.

403
00:22:57,584 --> 00:23:00,447
We can just see each other like this now.

404
00:23:00,447 --> 00:23:04,083
I'm just thrilled you're back in Korea.

405
00:23:04,083 --> 00:23:05,859
So today,

406
00:23:05,859 --> 00:23:07,983
it's my treat.

407
00:23:07,983 --> 00:23:09,748
Here, open up.

408
00:23:09,748 --> 00:23:12,132
- Here, careful.
- Ah.

409
00:23:16,193 --> 00:23:17,977
Soo Bin...

410
00:23:18,735 --> 00:23:21,392
is it still too hard for you to visit?

411
00:23:22,151 --> 00:23:24,304
Maybe next time.

412
00:23:24,304 --> 00:23:26,438
Your dad's...

413
00:23:27,234 --> 00:23:29,769
not doing this because he hates you.

414
00:23:29,769 --> 00:23:31,569
Mom, please.

415
00:23:35,401 --> 00:23:38,485
Okay. I'm sorry, son.

416
00:23:38,485 --> 00:23:40,748
Stop apologizing...

417
00:23:41,356 --> 00:23:43,170
and get in.

418
00:23:46,359 --> 00:23:48,496
Promise me you'll call
when you come down again.

419
00:23:48,496 --> 00:23:50,163
I'll be waiting.

420
00:23:50,163 --> 00:23:51,619
I will.

421
00:24:02,885 --> 00:24:04,587
Get home safe.

422
00:25:01,693 --> 00:25:05,009
[No Jaywalking]

423
00:25:07,950 --> 00:25:10,715
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

424
00:25:26,526 --> 00:25:27,552
<i>I'm not going.</i>

425
00:25:27,552 --> 00:25:29,818
<i>You promised! We'd make movies together!</i>

426
00:25:29,818 --> 00:25:31,939
<i>What does that matter?</i>

427
00:25:50,576 --> 00:25:52,920
What the hell are you doing?

428
00:26:50,261 --> 00:26:52,016
Are you okay?

429
00:26:54,359 --> 00:26:56,852
I just got a little dizzy.

430
00:27:12,610 --> 00:27:14,682
Hey.

431
00:27:14,682 --> 00:27:17,101
I eat carrots now.

432
00:27:17,996 --> 00:27:20,193
I realized I couldn't be a picky eater

433
00:27:20,193 --> 00:27:23,507
if I wanted to survive in this job.

434
00:27:24,568 --> 00:27:29,603
Enough time has passed
for us to change this much.

435
00:27:33,678 --> 00:27:35,979
But why are there...

436
00:27:37,277 --> 00:27:40,943
some things that never get better?

437
00:27:42,665 --> 00:27:46,240
Why do the good memories fade,

438
00:27:47,193 --> 00:27:49,551
but the bad ones...

439
00:27:50,245 --> 00:27:52,634
stay so vivid?

440
00:27:55,276 --> 00:27:58,233
Maybe that's why we have to hold on

441
00:27:58,233 --> 00:28:01,129
to the good ones even tighter.

442
00:28:06,942 --> 00:28:09,166
That's why I'm here.

443
00:28:24,897 --> 00:28:26,023
Yes, Producer.

444
00:28:26,023 --> 00:28:28,991
I just need to head to Jeonju Station, right?

445
00:29:01,139 --> 00:29:02,351
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

446
00:29:11,067 --> 00:29:14,573
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

447
00:29:17,950 --> 00:29:19,776
<i>The title is "Gyeongseong Love Song."</i>

448
00:29:19,776 --> 00:29:22,078
<i>Nan Young is a gisaeng
who dreams of becoming a poet.</i>

449
00:29:22,078 --> 00:29:26,124
<i>But after her best friend is shot and killed,</i>

450
00:29:26,124 --> 00:29:28,376
<i>she lives only for revenge.</i>

451
00:29:28,376 --> 00:29:30,396
[Written and Directed
by Ju Yi Jae & Woo Soo Bin]

452
00:29:37,552 --> 00:29:42,223
<i>Then, a man appears before her
like it's destiny.</i>

453
00:29:42,223 --> 00:29:44,816
<i>None other than the rich young master,
Moo Gyeom!</i>

454
00:29:44,816 --> 00:29:47,645
<i>You have to have the rich heir.</i>

455
00:29:47,645 --> 00:29:50,359
<i>Poetry, booze, and women.</i>

456
00:29:50,359 --> 00:29:53,942
<i>A guy who just enjoys life
without a single care in the world.</i>

457
00:29:53,942 --> 00:29:58,304
<i>How could anyone not fall for a guy like that?</i>

458
00:29:58,304 --> 00:30:00,449
<i>But here's the twist.</i>

459
00:30:00,449 --> 00:30:03,804
<i>He's actually a freedom fighter
hiding behind a playboy mask!</i>

460
00:30:03,804 --> 00:30:05,246
<i>Hold on, it gets better.</i>

461
00:30:05,246 --> 00:30:07,165
<i>The most shocking truth is...</i>

462
00:30:07,165 --> 00:30:11,064
<i>He's the exact enemy
Nan Young has been hunting her whole life.</i>

463
00:30:11,064 --> 00:30:14,735
<i>Revenge or love, that is the question.</i>

464
00:30:14,735 --> 00:30:17,114
<i>- Bang!
- Ugh.</i>

465
00:30:23,766 --> 00:30:27,067
<i>So... does someone end up dying?</i>

466
00:30:28,068 --> 00:30:29,395
<i>Someone has to.</i>

467
00:30:29,395 --> 00:30:31,702
<i>A romance needs to be tragic.</i>

468
00:30:33,777 --> 00:30:36,193
<i>I prefer happy endings, though.</i>

469
00:30:36,193 --> 00:30:41,855
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

470
00:31:10,610 --> 00:31:12,568
- Hey.
- Yeah?

471
00:31:12,568 --> 00:31:16,033
Remember when I came to you
about making movies?

472
00:31:17,276 --> 00:31:19,070
How could I forget?

473
00:31:19,070 --> 00:31:23,483
You showed up with no money, no bags,
just that one script in your hand.

474
00:31:23,483 --> 00:31:25,266
Exactly.

475
00:31:25,266 --> 00:31:27,286
Even when things got tough
and I wanted to quit,

476
00:31:27,286 --> 00:31:29,735
I held onto that script to keep going.

477
00:31:29,735 --> 00:31:31,927
That's why Yi Jae gave it to me.

478
00:31:31,927 --> 00:31:36,614
She was holding onto me so I wouldn't give up,

479
00:31:36,614 --> 00:31:38,680
asking me to keep dreaming together.

480
00:31:39,485 --> 00:31:40,587
I realized it way too late.

481
00:31:40,587 --> 00:31:43,636
And that's exactly
why you worked like crazy to get here.

482
00:31:43,636 --> 00:31:46,265
Is that why I lost her?

483
00:31:46,265 --> 00:31:49,816
I made it this far because of that script,

484
00:31:50,522 --> 00:31:52,687
but maybe having it in my hands is

485
00:31:52,687 --> 00:31:55,822
the exact reason Yi Jae ended up
giving up on everything.

486
00:31:58,901 --> 00:32:00,905
I have no idea what you're talking about.

487
00:32:00,905 --> 00:32:03,038
Just eat your food.

488
00:32:03,729 --> 00:32:08,169
I gave the "Gyeongseong Love Song" script
back to her.

489
00:32:08,169 --> 00:32:11,401
- But she hasn't called me yet.
- What?

490
00:32:11,401 --> 00:32:13,234
Please.

491
00:32:13,234 --> 00:32:14,950
Hold on. What if...

492
00:32:14,950 --> 00:32:16,529
No.

493
00:32:16,529 --> 00:32:18,423
She knows how much that script means to us.

494
00:32:18,423 --> 00:32:19,588
There's no way she'd throw it out.

495
00:32:19,588 --> 00:32:22,341
But the bottom line is,
you don't actually have it on you right now.

496
00:32:22,341 --> 00:32:25,316
- Yeah.
- Okay, that's it. I'm heading back.

497
00:32:25,316 --> 00:32:27,651
I haven't found soft tofu stew
better than LA's anyway,

498
00:32:27,651 --> 00:32:29,640
and I'm sick of you.

499
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:32,435
I'm officially giving up my dream
of going independent right here.

500
00:32:32,435 --> 00:32:34,715
I'm leaving. I'm out.

501
00:32:34,715 --> 00:32:37,364
You scanned it, right?

502
00:32:38,335 --> 00:32:40,067
Me?

503
00:32:40,067 --> 00:32:41,195
No.

504
00:32:41,195 --> 00:32:43,988
Man.

505
00:32:43,988 --> 00:32:47,165
You're taking this joke way too far.

506
00:32:48,610 --> 00:32:50,565
You're kidding, right?

507
00:32:51,998 --> 00:32:54,421
Just a little closer.

508
00:32:54,421 --> 00:32:55,822
- See you later.
- See you later.

509
00:32:55,822 --> 00:32:57,801
See you later.

510
00:33:05,526 --> 00:33:07,887
Congratulations on your wedding.

511
00:33:07,887 --> 00:33:10,068
Thank you.

512
00:33:10,068 --> 00:33:12,065
These are gorgeous.

513
00:33:13,809 --> 00:33:15,855
Orders just came down from headquarters.

514
00:33:15,855 --> 00:33:17,922
We're going with Plan B.

515
00:33:25,838 --> 00:33:27,178
Cut!

516
00:33:27,178 --> 00:33:28,518
Okay.

517
00:33:28,518 --> 00:33:30,449
Alright, we're breaking for lunch.

518
00:33:30,449 --> 00:33:32,234
- Enjoy your lunch.
- Enjoy.

519
00:33:32,234 --> 00:33:35,247
How did that take look?

520
00:33:35,247 --> 00:33:36,332
Thank you.

521
00:33:36,332 --> 00:33:38,598
- Five rolls of gimbap.
- Yeah.

522
00:33:38,598 --> 00:33:40,259
Wait, what? Five rolls?

523
00:33:40,259 --> 00:33:41,599
That Go Sang Yeon...

524
00:33:41,599 --> 00:33:42,819
I grabbed yours for you, though.

525
00:33:42,819 --> 00:33:44,659
And you should eat in the van.

526
00:33:44,659 --> 00:33:46,610
The CEO specifically said
you have to eat inside.

527
00:33:46,610 --> 00:33:48,543
- She told me to tell you...
- I'm eating outside.

528
00:33:48,543 --> 00:33:49,928
But that dress is so uncomfortable.

529
00:33:49,928 --> 00:33:51,559
Just get in and eat with me...

530
00:33:51,559 --> 00:33:53,516
I could do a backflip in this thing.

531
00:33:53,516 --> 00:33:55,299
Don't worry about me and go eat

532
00:33:55,299 --> 00:33:57,438
before Sang Yeon gobbles everything up.

533
00:33:57,438 --> 00:34:00,198
But your dress...

534
00:34:22,723 --> 00:34:24,580
What?

535
00:34:26,842 --> 00:34:28,398
Never mind.

536
00:34:39,193 --> 00:34:42,113
I seriously don't want to film right now.

537
00:34:44,151 --> 00:34:45,613
Sorry?

538
00:34:48,359 --> 00:34:51,234
Is it so wrong to not want to shoot?

539
00:34:51,234 --> 00:34:52,777
No,

540
00:34:52,777 --> 00:34:54,579
that's completely fair.

541
00:34:58,234 --> 00:35:00,835
You didn't get one of these?

542
00:35:00,835 --> 00:35:03,677
Yeah, they said they ran out.

543
00:35:04,651 --> 00:35:06,723
That jerk, Go Sang Yeon.

544
00:35:09,026 --> 00:35:10,693
- Want some?
- I'm good.

545
00:35:10,693 --> 00:35:12,386
I can't finish a whole roll anyway.

546
00:35:12,386 --> 00:35:14,022
Just eat it.

547
00:35:15,058 --> 00:35:17,357
My arm's getting tired.

548
00:35:18,058 --> 00:35:19,661
Well...

549
00:35:20,485 --> 00:35:22,525
Thank you.

550
00:35:43,082 --> 00:35:44,902
You're bored too, right?

551
00:35:44,902 --> 00:35:47,171
Gang Member Number 3.

552
00:35:47,171 --> 00:35:48,962
I actually need to get going.

553
00:35:48,962 --> 00:35:51,062
What?

554
00:35:51,062 --> 00:35:52,642
You're done right after lunch?

555
00:35:52,642 --> 00:35:54,011
Lucky you.

556
00:35:54,011 --> 00:35:57,314
I actually can't leave right now
because of you, Ha Na-nim.

557
00:35:58,351 --> 00:36:01,002
Adding "nim" makes me sound like God.

558
00:36:01,002 --> 00:36:03,242
I'm Buddhist.

559
00:36:03,242 --> 00:36:06,524
Just call me Ha Na.

560
00:36:06,524 --> 00:36:08,049
Right.

561
00:36:09,026 --> 00:36:12,322
That thing you're sitting on is...

562
00:36:12,322 --> 00:36:14,355
my bike.

563
00:36:19,568 --> 00:36:21,191
- Hop on, then.
- What?

564
00:36:21,191 --> 00:36:23,840
Could you just take me for a quick spin?

565
00:36:24,443 --> 00:36:26,252
Come on, I gave you my gimbap.

566
00:36:26,252 --> 00:36:28,420
Just ten minutes.

567
00:36:28,420 --> 00:36:30,234
Or five?

568
00:36:30,234 --> 00:36:33,190
I'll call it even for the food.

569
00:36:33,190 --> 00:36:35,060
Sweet!

570
00:36:39,777 --> 00:36:41,463
Like this?

571
00:37:02,026 --> 00:37:04,485
It's just like "A Moment of Romance" today!

572
00:37:04,485 --> 00:37:07,234
What? A moment of what?

573
00:37:07,234 --> 00:37:09,469
That Hong Kong movie...

574
00:37:10,587 --> 00:37:12,602
Never mind.

575
00:37:24,651 --> 00:37:26,276
Whoa, whoa!

576
00:37:26,276 --> 00:37:29,951
Did you see that? I almost just died!

577
00:37:29,951 --> 00:37:32,276
If I'd looked back, we'd both be dead.

578
00:37:32,276 --> 00:37:35,370
- Hold on tight.
- Okay!

579
00:37:53,228 --> 00:37:55,443
I finally feel alive again.

580
00:37:55,443 --> 00:37:57,609
Thanks, Yu Geon.

581
00:37:58,984 --> 00:38:00,318
Chae Yeon!

582
00:38:00,318 --> 00:38:01,555
Ha Na.

583
00:38:01,555 --> 00:38:02,989
Where have you been?

584
00:38:02,989 --> 00:38:04,735
I've been looking everywhere for you!

585
00:38:04,735 --> 00:38:07,110
<i>She actually remembered my name.</i>

586
00:38:08,735 --> 00:38:10,319
Look at the state of you!

587
00:38:10,319 --> 00:38:11,399
What is that on your head?

588
00:38:11,399 --> 00:38:12,694
A helmet.

589
00:38:12,694 --> 00:38:13,859
Wait.

590
00:38:13,859 --> 00:38:15,539
The helmet...

591
00:38:29,526 --> 00:38:30,718
Ma'am.

592
00:38:30,718 --> 00:38:32,338
Ma'am!

593
00:38:32,338 --> 00:38:34,840
Producer Jaden just landed.

594
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:38,359
- What?
- Producer Jaden just landed.

595
00:38:38,359 --> 00:38:42,197
Should I book that sushi place
in Cheongdam for the meeting?

596
00:38:42,197 --> 00:38:44,859
- Why there?
- You said it was the best sushi of your life.

597
00:38:44,859 --> 00:38:49,790
Why would I take a Korean-American
to my all-time favorite sushi place?

598
00:38:49,790 --> 00:38:51,357
Word is he likes Korean food.

599
00:38:51,357 --> 00:38:53,297
Book a traditional Korean restaurant.

600
00:38:53,297 --> 00:38:55,798
- One that has really nice side dishes.
- Yes.

601
00:38:55,798 --> 00:38:58,217
- And about the meeting with Writer Noh...
- Hey!

602
00:38:58,217 --> 00:39:00,663
Ugh, just text it to me.

603
00:39:01,279 --> 00:39:03,870
Who on earth named this thing
the "Stairway to Heaven?"

604
00:39:03,870 --> 00:39:06,628
I'm staring straight at the gates of hell.

605
00:39:08,347 --> 00:39:11,792
Anyway, where did Ha Na run off to
in the middle of all this?

606
00:39:11,792 --> 00:39:13,859
Well...

607
00:39:13,859 --> 00:39:16,357
she was looking for someone.

608
00:39:18,984 --> 00:39:21,399
- And?
- So I found him for her.

609
00:39:21,399 --> 00:39:24,234
Just tell me who it is!

610
00:39:24,234 --> 00:39:26,022
Well...

611
00:39:28,726 --> 00:39:31,371
Are we playing "Twenty Questions" right now?

612
00:39:56,477 --> 00:39:58,721
Who are you?

613
00:40:06,401 --> 00:40:08,355
I came to return this.

614
00:40:10,735 --> 00:40:13,194
Something smells really good.

615
00:40:14,359 --> 00:40:17,323
I just got off my shift at a BBQ joint.

616
00:40:18,276 --> 00:40:20,651
By the way,

617
00:40:20,651 --> 00:40:23,329
the sunset from up here is gorgeous.

618
00:40:26,431 --> 00:40:28,512
How long have you been waiting here?

619
00:40:28,512 --> 00:40:30,651
You literally see me up there every single day.

620
00:40:30,651 --> 00:40:32,839
How are you not a fan?

621
00:40:42,693 --> 00:40:46,728
How did you even find my place?

622
00:40:50,735 --> 00:40:52,292
From this.

623
00:40:56,897 --> 00:40:58,744
[Sim Yu Geon]

624
00:41:00,028 --> 00:41:02,027
But my address isn't even on this.

625
00:41:02,027 --> 00:41:03,612
I can't stop thinking about it.

626
00:41:03,612 --> 00:41:05,560
Sorry? Thinking about what?

627
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:08,291
Riding on your bike.

628
00:41:09,368 --> 00:41:12,462
I've never felt anything like that before.

629
00:41:16,359 --> 00:41:19,469
Could you take me for another spin sometime?

630
00:41:20,526 --> 00:41:22,098
Sure.

631
00:41:22,759 --> 00:41:24,568
But...

632
00:41:24,568 --> 00:41:26,999
why are you doing this?

633
00:41:26,999 --> 00:41:28,303
What's wrong with that?

634
00:41:28,303 --> 00:41:31,016
It's just...

635
00:41:31,016 --> 00:41:32,909
you're kind of scaring me.

636
00:41:34,234 --> 00:41:35,448
I'm scaring you?

637
00:41:35,448 --> 00:41:36,469
Well, it's just...

638
00:41:36,469 --> 00:41:39,474
This kind of stuff always works on TV.

639
00:41:39,474 --> 00:41:40,849
Works? What do you mean?

640
00:41:40,849 --> 00:41:43,128
I guess that only works on TV.

641
00:41:43,128 --> 00:41:46,318
Look, as you probably know,
I'm actually amazing at everything else.

642
00:41:46,318 --> 00:41:49,069
I can do forward rolls,
shoot a gun, ride horses,

643
00:41:49,069 --> 00:41:51,702
and even jump off high buildings.

644
00:41:51,702 --> 00:41:53,778
- Right.
- But...

645
00:41:55,068 --> 00:41:57,966
I have absolutely no idea how to make friends.

646
00:41:58,568 --> 00:42:01,177
Which is why I don't have any.

647
00:42:08,221 --> 00:42:09,983
Are you saying

648
00:42:10,603 --> 00:42:13,231
you want to be friends with me?

649
00:42:16,651 --> 00:42:18,328
I guess...

650
00:42:23,193 --> 00:42:24,735
Yeah.

651
00:42:24,735 --> 00:42:28,005
Then let's be...

652
00:42:28,005 --> 00:42:29,644
friends.

653
00:42:31,910 --> 00:42:33,568
You mean it?

654
00:42:33,568 --> 00:42:35,153
Yeah.

655
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:42,176
Then consider this
a gift to celebrate our new friendship.

656
00:42:43,818 --> 00:42:44,942
Huh?

657
00:42:44,942 --> 00:42:46,818
I...

658
00:42:46,818 --> 00:42:49,429
I have to go now, friend.

659
00:42:49,429 --> 00:42:50,651
Bye.

660
00:42:50,651 --> 00:42:53,461
Bye, friend.

661
00:42:56,526 --> 00:43:00,236
Seems like she knows
exactly how to make friends.

662
00:43:22,201 --> 00:43:23,542
It's been a while, Jaden.

663
00:43:23,542 --> 00:43:25,022
Hello, CEO An.

664
00:43:25,022 --> 00:43:29,967
Or should I be calling you CEO Seo now?

665
00:43:29,967 --> 00:43:31,341
Whatever you're comfortable with.

666
00:43:31,341 --> 00:43:34,102
I never thought I'd see the day
you'd be smiling in front of me.

667
00:43:34,102 --> 00:43:37,933
Did that day come sooner than you expected?

668
00:43:37,933 --> 00:43:40,687
You've grown a thick skin.

669
00:43:40,687 --> 00:43:44,272
It's nice to see
you've lost some of that innocence.

670
00:43:44,272 --> 00:43:46,701
Let's order first.

671
00:43:46,701 --> 00:43:50,661
Talking business on an empty stomach
makes me nauseous.

672
00:44:00,372 --> 00:44:02,215
Here, let me.

673
00:44:04,777 --> 00:44:09,861
So, you're saying you're open to co-producing?

674
00:44:09,861 --> 00:44:11,800
Since I'm starting out in unfamiliar territory,

675
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:14,344
I wanted someone I could trust to guide me.

676
00:44:14,344 --> 00:44:17,722
And you think I'm the right person for that?

677
00:44:17,722 --> 00:44:20,726
You're the one who reached out to me first.

678
00:44:20,726 --> 00:44:22,521
How naive.

679
00:44:22,521 --> 00:44:25,315
You have no idea what I might demand.

680
00:44:25,315 --> 00:44:29,386
Let's save the project talk
for when the first draft is ready.

681
00:44:31,030 --> 00:44:35,241
I'm actually much more interested
in the off-screen drama.

682
00:44:35,241 --> 00:44:36,982
How much are you willing to share with me?

683
00:44:36,982 --> 00:44:40,920
I'd be happy to share everything I know.

684
00:44:41,621 --> 00:44:43,702
I heard there's quite a backstory
to that script.

685
00:44:43,702 --> 00:44:47,361
Rumors say it involves a first love?

686
00:44:47,361 --> 00:44:51,548
That only applies
if we're official partners, though.

687
00:44:51,548 --> 00:44:53,594
Since we're not there yet,

688
00:44:53,594 --> 00:44:57,228
I need to be a bit careful.

689
00:45:09,914 --> 00:45:13,154
I'll reach out as soon
as the first draft is ready.

690
00:45:13,154 --> 00:45:14,687
Sounds good.

691
00:45:34,984 --> 00:45:37,369
- Hey.
- Yes?

692
00:45:37,369 --> 00:45:40,769
Why'd he come all this way
if he wasn't coming in?

693
00:45:40,769 --> 00:45:43,149
Maybe he's just uncomfortable?

694
00:45:45,151 --> 00:45:47,769
Uncomfortable? About what?

695
00:45:47,769 --> 00:45:49,822
I'm sorry.

696
00:45:55,401 --> 00:45:57,367
You don't have to walk on eggshells around me.

697
00:45:57,367 --> 00:45:59,369
You said CEO An is our best bet anyway.

698
00:45:59,369 --> 00:46:02,068
Yeah, for now, she is.

699
00:46:02,068 --> 00:46:06,130
And I'm not walking on eggshells.
I'm actually really pissed off right now.

700
00:46:07,859 --> 00:46:10,526
You need to get that script back from Yi Jae.

701
00:46:10,526 --> 00:46:12,185
- Why?
- What do you mean, why?

702
00:46:12,185 --> 00:46:16,464
You went on TV and blabbed all about a script
without even having a first draft.

703
00:46:16,464 --> 00:46:18,545
Every single person I meet brings it up.

704
00:46:18,545 --> 00:46:21,646
CEO An even brought up the first love rumor.

705
00:46:22,304 --> 00:46:24,391
Don't tell me...

706
00:46:24,391 --> 00:46:25,600
In Uk.

707
00:46:25,600 --> 00:46:27,505
Yes, I said it was me.

708
00:46:27,505 --> 00:46:30,196
I told her I was your first love.

709
00:46:34,151 --> 00:46:35,155
[Yi Jae]

710
00:46:38,735 --> 00:46:40,694
Yeah, hello?

711
00:46:40,694 --> 00:46:42,909
<i>Where are you? Get to Sangam right now.</i>

712
00:46:42,909 --> 00:46:44,414
<i>Producer Kyung wants a meeting.</i>

713
00:46:44,414 --> 00:46:46,629
<i>I'll text you the address.</i>

714
00:46:48,109 --> 00:46:49,615
Why are you going to a meeting?

715
00:46:49,615 --> 00:46:52,755
I have no idea why
you're even going to a meeting. Whatever.

716
00:46:52,755 --> 00:46:54,474
Just go

717
00:46:54,474 --> 00:46:56,801
and make sure that script is still alive.

718
00:46:56,801 --> 00:46:59,401
- Yes, boss.
- Right.

719
00:46:59,401 --> 00:47:01,200
Please get out.

720
00:47:16,946 --> 00:47:19,203
My phone!

721
00:47:34,443 --> 00:47:35,901
It's still early, let's get another round.

722
00:47:35,901 --> 00:47:37,859
That's enough. Your taxi's here.

723
00:47:37,859 --> 00:47:39,443
- Here!
- Who called it?

724
00:47:39,443 --> 00:47:41,151
- I did.
- You shouldn't have!

725
00:47:41,151 --> 00:47:42,401
Let's get one more round.

726
00:47:42,401 --> 00:47:44,682
Back to your wife you go.

727
00:47:44,682 --> 00:47:45,984
I don't want to go home

728
00:47:45,984 --> 00:47:48,433
- because of my wife.
- But you love her!

729
00:47:48,433 --> 00:47:50,644
Hey! I do not!

730
00:47:50,644 --> 00:47:53,443
- Make sure he gets home safe.
- Sure.

731
00:47:53,443 --> 00:47:55,735
- Alright.
- Seriously...

732
00:47:55,735 --> 00:47:59,201
I'm not going home!

733
00:48:02,157 --> 00:48:03,198
Wait, what?

734
00:48:03,198 --> 00:48:05,610
I thought we were having a meeting.

735
00:48:05,610 --> 00:48:07,078
- Huh?
- Is everyone gone?

736
00:48:07,078 --> 00:48:09,117
It's over.

737
00:48:09,117 --> 00:48:11,164
Why are you so late?

738
00:48:11,164 --> 00:48:13,920
You call this late?
I even printed out the prep sheets.

739
00:48:13,920 --> 00:48:15,018
And I called him, too.

740
00:48:15,018 --> 00:48:18,004
"Him?" Why did you bring a dog? Where is he?

741
00:48:18,004 --> 00:48:20,568
Woo Soo Bin. Director Ian Woo.

742
00:48:20,568 --> 00:48:23,109
Oh, him.

743
00:48:23,109 --> 00:48:26,346
Hey, he already agreed to do the show,

744
00:48:26,346 --> 00:48:27,889
so we're good.

745
00:48:27,889 --> 00:48:32,359
I'll take it from here, so you stay out of it.

746
00:48:32,359 --> 00:48:34,425
Since when do you handle things yourself?

747
00:48:34,425 --> 00:48:37,064
Did you even have a meeting today?

748
00:48:37,064 --> 00:48:39,985
Wait, did you just call me
to be your designated driver?

749
00:48:39,985 --> 00:48:42,119
Designated driver?

750
00:48:43,026 --> 00:48:45,498
Ding, ding, ding.

751
00:48:46,151 --> 00:48:48,702
Your driving is more comfortable

752
00:48:48,702 --> 00:48:51,884
than my own mattress.

753
00:48:51,884 --> 00:48:54,489
I'm counting on you.

754
00:48:57,777 --> 00:49:00,045
- She can't drive.
- Excuse me?

755
00:49:00,045 --> 00:49:01,901
She's been drinking.

756
00:49:01,901 --> 00:49:03,635
Huh?

757
00:49:03,635 --> 00:49:06,697
You had drinks with me, remember?

758
00:49:09,306 --> 00:49:10,863
I'm so dizzy.

759
00:49:10,863 --> 00:49:12,304
How am I even here?

760
00:49:12,304 --> 00:49:14,043
Why am I here?

761
00:49:14,043 --> 00:49:15,902
How did I get here? So dizzy...

762
00:49:15,902 --> 00:49:18,690
You were completely fine a second ago.
What are you talking about?

763
00:49:18,690 --> 00:49:20,684
This is why day drinking is the worst.

764
00:49:20,684 --> 00:49:23,659
I guess I do smell alcohol.

765
00:49:29,777 --> 00:49:30,859
Is he always like this?

766
00:49:30,859 --> 00:49:32,067
What?

767
00:49:32,067 --> 00:49:33,079
No, well...

768
00:49:33,079 --> 00:49:35,651
he does make me work when he's drunk,
dumps his crap on me,

769
00:49:35,651 --> 00:49:37,528
- and uses me as his driver, but...
- What?

770
00:49:37,528 --> 00:49:39,777
Hey! Ju Yi Jae!

771
00:49:39,777 --> 00:49:41,828
Still, he's not a bad guy.

772
00:49:41,828 --> 00:49:43,276
We've been friends since college,

773
00:49:43,276 --> 00:49:45,175
- almost a decade?
- Right?

774
00:49:45,175 --> 00:49:47,429
No. He really is a bad guy.

775
00:49:47,429 --> 00:49:48,639
Excuse me,

776
00:49:48,639 --> 00:49:51,688
what do you think
you're doing right in front of me?

777
00:49:51,688 --> 00:49:53,808
Then what exactly are you doing to Yi Jae?

778
00:49:53,808 --> 00:49:55,401
What?

779
00:49:55,401 --> 00:49:57,897
What are you talking about?

780
00:49:58,523 --> 00:50:00,434
I already know everything.

781
00:50:00,434 --> 00:50:03,294
Should I say it,
or do you want to tell her yourself?

782
00:50:03,294 --> 00:50:06,874
<i>They're canceling "Here Comes Yi Jae"
in the upcoming revamp.</i>

783
00:50:06,874 --> 00:50:08,715
<i>Can't you just do a better job, man?</i>

784
00:50:08,715 --> 00:50:12,735
<i>People are saying the producer is
riding the reporter's coattails.</i>

785
00:50:12,735 --> 00:50:14,335
<i>Just keep the ratings up.</i>

786
00:50:14,335 --> 00:50:16,015
<i>Even better if we hit a record high.</i>

787
00:50:16,015 --> 00:50:20,919
<i>Do that, and I'll make sure
your job is safe no matter what.</i>

788
00:50:20,919 --> 00:50:23,963
<i>I'll do my best.</i>

789
00:50:23,963 --> 00:50:25,763
I was just...

790
00:50:28,984 --> 00:50:31,163
Forget it.

791
00:50:31,163 --> 00:50:33,068
I'll hear it straight from him.

792
00:50:33,068 --> 00:50:34,777
Get in.

793
00:50:34,777 --> 00:50:36,068
What?

794
00:50:36,068 --> 00:50:37,485
I said, get in.

795
00:50:37,485 --> 00:50:39,597
Okay.

796
00:50:52,151 --> 00:50:53,701
I thought you were drinking.

797
00:50:53,701 --> 00:50:55,233
I didn't drink.

798
00:50:55,233 --> 00:50:57,038
Give me a straight answer.

799
00:50:57,038 --> 00:50:59,693
This is my mom's car!
I'm still making payments...

800
00:50:59,693 --> 00:51:00,901
What? Am I getting fired?

801
00:51:00,901 --> 00:51:02,968
I think I'm going to throw up.

802
00:51:06,422 --> 00:51:08,040
Hey, this...

803
00:51:12,526 --> 00:51:15,397
And you totally used me.

804
00:51:16,056 --> 00:51:17,461
Hey.

805
00:51:18,109 --> 00:51:19,790
Hey!

806
00:51:19,790 --> 00:51:21,890
Look, I'm sorry.

807
00:51:21,890 --> 00:51:25,608
But I had to save my own skin...

808
00:51:25,608 --> 00:51:28,901
No, that's not what I meant...

809
00:51:28,901 --> 00:51:31,163
Hey, watch the road!

810
00:51:33,984 --> 00:51:36,627
Watch out!

811
00:51:54,193 --> 00:51:58,211
Since when did you write me off?

812
00:51:58,211 --> 00:52:02,061
I know I could get fired at any moment,

813
00:52:02,061 --> 00:52:03,396
but this is crossing the line.

814
00:52:03,396 --> 00:52:05,726
Hey, Yi Jae...

815
00:52:05,726 --> 00:52:06,941
just listen to me.

816
00:52:06,941 --> 00:52:10,276
Hey, where are you going?

817
00:52:10,276 --> 00:52:12,735
What?

818
00:52:12,735 --> 00:52:15,331
You and I are done as of today.

819
00:52:15,331 --> 00:52:16,408
- Get out.
- Huh?

820
00:52:16,408 --> 00:52:17,485
I said, get out!

821
00:52:17,485 --> 00:52:18,620
Hey, hold on a second.

822
00:52:18,620 --> 00:52:20,818
- Get the hell out!
- No!

823
00:52:20,818 --> 00:52:22,874
Get out!

824
00:52:22,874 --> 00:52:24,777
Oh, no...

825
00:52:24,777 --> 00:52:26,302
I didn't...

826
00:52:26,302 --> 00:52:27,715
- Come here.
- I'll sew it up for you.

827
00:52:27,715 --> 00:52:29,995
Come here. Get out!

828
00:52:29,995 --> 00:52:31,557
Get out!

829
00:52:33,942 --> 00:52:36,006
Hey.

830
00:52:36,006 --> 00:52:37,818
Hey.

831
00:52:37,818 --> 00:52:39,151
My keys...

832
00:52:39,151 --> 00:52:40,194
Hey, what are you doing?

833
00:52:40,194 --> 00:52:42,151
Hey!

834
00:52:44,270 --> 00:52:45,888
No!

835
00:52:46,568 --> 00:52:49,199
You crazy...

836
00:52:51,698 --> 00:52:53,989
Hey! My keys...

837
00:52:58,026 --> 00:52:59,901
Where are they?

838
00:52:59,901 --> 00:53:02,963
Hey! Ju Yi Jae!

839
00:53:50,651 --> 00:53:52,610
I feel like...

840
00:53:52,610 --> 00:53:55,887
I've been rushing through life,

841
00:53:55,887 --> 00:53:59,103
just putting out fires as they come.

842
00:53:59,984 --> 00:54:02,890
Who would've thought
a job I took just for the money

843
00:54:02,890 --> 00:54:08,229
would turn into weeks, months, and years?

844
00:54:08,229 --> 00:54:11,198
That alone is impressive.

845
00:54:12,568 --> 00:54:14,693
That's why so many places want to book you.

846
00:54:14,693 --> 00:54:16,401
But...

847
00:54:16,401 --> 00:54:19,039
I'm not irreplaceable.

848
00:54:20,167 --> 00:54:24,187
Who else is going to show up
on "Here Comes Yi Jae" if you don't?

849
00:54:24,187 --> 00:54:25,922
You're right.

850
00:54:27,109 --> 00:54:29,208
I gave it the wrong title.

851
00:54:29,208 --> 00:54:31,469
I said "Here Comes Yi Jae!"

852
00:54:31,469 --> 00:54:33,838
and now I'm just gone.

853
00:54:35,969 --> 00:54:40,457
I didn't love the job,
but it meant a lot to me.

854
00:54:42,016 --> 00:54:46,608
It put food on the table and paid off my debts.

855
00:55:00,151 --> 00:55:02,044
You jerk.

856
00:55:03,693 --> 00:55:05,777
Why do you keep following me around?

857
00:55:05,777 --> 00:55:08,088
You won't even let me cry in peace.

858
00:55:33,918 --> 00:55:35,908
Ju Yi Jae.

859
00:55:44,443 --> 00:55:47,794
Now I see why you said
being pathetic is the worst.

860
00:55:49,568 --> 00:55:52,299
Because it stays with you forever.

861
00:55:57,026 --> 00:55:59,139
You do look...

862
00:56:00,485 --> 00:56:03,136
a bit pathetic...

863
00:56:03,136 --> 00:56:04,738
right now.

864
00:56:09,237 --> 00:56:12,025
Not that I could ever forget you anyway.

865
00:56:25,702 --> 00:56:27,497
Woo Soo Bin.

866
00:56:29,109 --> 00:56:32,047
My biggest regret isn't you.

867
00:56:33,777 --> 00:56:35,547
It's me.

868
00:58:17,401 --> 00:58:19,178
Ian.

869
00:58:25,401 --> 00:58:26,777
Let's go get some breakfast.

870
00:58:26,777 --> 00:58:28,520
In Uk.

871
00:58:34,193 --> 00:58:35,791
It's freezing.

872
00:59:36,513 --> 00:59:37,892
<i>I look forward to working with you.</i>

873
00:59:37,892 --> 00:59:41,065
<i>Please stay at the hotel
just until the studio is set up.</i>

874
00:59:41,065 --> 00:59:42,692
<i>You need to write.</i>

875
00:59:42,692 --> 00:59:44,433
<i>You were laughing at me earlier, weren't you?</i>

876
00:59:44,433 --> 00:59:46,073
<i>Who do you think you are,
messing with my friend?</i>

877
00:59:46,073 --> 00:59:47,693
<i>Come on, friend. Let's go.</i>

878
00:59:47,693 --> 00:59:51,113
<i>When you're stuck in the same house
and spending all day together,</i>

879
00:59:51,113 --> 00:59:53,449
<i>you naturally catch feelings,</i>

880
00:59:53,449 --> 00:59:57,072
<i>and it turns into a hot, R-rated romance.</i>

881
00:59:57,072 --> 00:59:59,151
<i>What are you even hesitating for?</i>

882
00:59:59,151 --> 01:00:00,777
<i>Looks like...</i>

883
01:00:00,777 --> 01:00:02,966
<i>we're about to do it right now.</i>
